OL,3,CYousaf warns against using new hate
OL,4,Ccrime law to make 'vexatious'
OL,5,Ccomplaints
OL,7,F"I would say to anybody who thinks
OL,8,Fthey are a victim of hatred, we take
OL,9,Fthat seriously, if you felt you are a
OL,10,Fvictim of hatred, then of course
OL,11,Freporting that to police is the right
OL,12,Fthing to do," he said.
OL,14,F"If you're thinking about making a a
OL,15,Fvexatious complaint, if you're
OL,16,Fthinking about making a complaint and
OL,17,Fthere's no merit in that, then do know
OL,18,Fthat the police will take that serious
OL,19,Fin terms of tackling vexatious
OL,20,Fcomplaints and so I would urge you not
OL,21,Fto do it."
